From: Namecoin Integration <namecoin-integration@example.com>
Date: 2026-04-16
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] netwerk/dns: Add .bit to effective_tld_names.dat

Adds "bit" to the Public Suffix List so Firefox treats .bit as a proper
effective TLD. Without this, Firefox would treat "example.bit" as having
an eTLD of "bit" but share cookies/origins across all .bit domains.

This ensures:
  - Proper origin isolation: example.bit ≠ other.bit
  - Cookie scope respects .bit boundaries
  - SameSite cookie attributes work correctly for .bit domains
  - Prevents cross-.bit domain tracking via shared storage

The entry is placed in the "ICANN DOMAINS" section near the end of the
TLD list, with a comment referencing the Namecoin feature flag to help
maintainers when the PSL is updated upstream.

Ongoing maintenance note: When effective_tld_names.dat is updated from
the upstream Public Suffix List (PSL), this entry must be re-added.
A comment marker "NAMECOIN_INTEGRATION" is included to make grep-based
detection easy in automated rebase scripts.

Bug: <to be filed on bugzilla.mozilla.org>
Reviewed-by: <pending>

---
 netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat b/netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat
index a1b2c3d4..e5f6a7b8 100644
--- a/netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat
+++ b/netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat
@@ -12000,6 +12000,14 @@ aw
 // Amazon : https://www.amazon.com/
 z-1.a9.com
 
+// BEGIN NAMECOIN_INTEGRATION
+// Namecoin decentralized DNS (.bit TLD)
+// See: https://namecoin.org/
+// Feature flag: network.namecoin.enabled (about:config)
+// Ensures proper origin isolation for .bit domains.
+// Must be preserved when updating this file from the upstream PSL.
+bit
+// END NAMECOIN_INTEGRATION
+
 // === END ICANN DOMAINS ===
 
 // === BEGIN PRIVATE DOMAINS ===
